The Vice President, Mike Pence, visited the Proton Therapy Institute at Hampton University in Virginia. He praised the institute for its contribution to healthcare and education, particularly as a historically black college. Pence also acknowledged the role of Dr. Harvey, the university's leader, in securing permanent federal funding for HBCUs. He highlighted the university's rich history, including its famous alumni such as Booker T. Washington. Pence expressed admiration for the institute's pioneering work in proton therapy, a cutting-edge cancer treatment. He pledged support for Hampton University and the Proton Therapy Institute, and was accompanied by Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos.